AB Foods, Barclays, BSkyB, Burberry: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-15T06:42:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/ab-foods-barclays-bskyb-burberry-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and
Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last market close.  The FTSE 100 Index advanced 52.77, or 1 percent, to
5,227.02 yesterday. The FTSE All-Share Index rose 1 percent
while Ireland’s ISEQ Index gained 2.1 percent.  Associated British Foods Plc (ABF)  : UBS AG upgraded the
shares to “buy” from “neutral.” The stock rose 0.6 percent
to 1,066 pence.  Barclays Plc (BARC)  ,  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  : Nomura
Holdings Inc. raised its recommendations for the U.K. banks to
“buy” from “neutral.”  Separately, Barclays defeated a bid by Lehman Brothers
Holdings Inc. to recover $500 million from the British bank in a
dispute over the bankruptcy sale of Lehman operations in 2008.
Barclays rose 2.5 percent to 152 pence while HSBC increased 0.5
percent to 501.5 pence.  British Sky Broadcasting Group Plc (BSY)  : Morgan Stanley
upgraded the U.K.’s largest pay-television provider to
“overweight” from “equal weight.” The shares rose 3 percent
to 702 pence.  Burberry Group Plc (BRBY)  : The National Business Daily
reported that China may issue a plan to cut luxury-goods taxes
by year end, citing an unidentified person familiar with the
situation. Shares of Burberry, the U.K.’s largest luxury-goods
maker, gained 5.6 percent to 1,367 pence.  Kingfisher Plc (KGF)  : Europe’s largest home-improvement
retailer reported a 24 percent gain in first-half adjusted
pretax profit rose to 439 million pounds ($692 million). That
beat the average analyst estimate of 408 million pounds. The
shares rose 2.4 percent to 239.6 pence.  Mitchells & Butlers Plc (MAB)  : Piedmont Inc., which
holds a 22.8 percent stake in the company, denied it said it
won’t increase its offer price over 230 pence a share. It
reserves the right to increase its offer if a bid were to be
made, the company said. Mitchells shares climbed 3.6 percent to
260 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
